{"sequence": 18, "timestamp": "2026-06-21T17:13:06.326864+00:00", "event_type": "session_decision_updated", "data": {"op": "session_decision_updated", "session_id": "sess_20260621_prod_19ecb9", "key": "task_failure", "value": {"task_a0b6ce": {"spec": "Wave 3: Add OAuth 2.1 JWT auth to snodo serve --tunnel\n\nCreate snodo/infrastructure/jwks.py with JwksClient class (fetch JWKS, cache RS256 key kid=mcp-auth-rs256-v1, verify Bearer JWTs)\n\nCreate snodo/infrastructure/oauth_verifier.py with JwksTokenVerifier (implements FastMCP TokenVerifier protocol)\n\nModify snodo/mcp/transport.py - build_fastmcp_server accepts optional token_verifier and auth_settings kwargs, passes them to FastMCP()\n\nModify snodo/cli/commands/serve_cmd.py - _run_server checks SNODO_TUNNEL_HOSTNAME env var, sets up OAuth if present; _run_tunnel sets the env var; _print_first_run_info shows OAuth instead of CF-Access\n\nCreate tests/infrastructure/test_jwks.py and tests/mcp/test_auth.py\n\nVerify with ruff check snodo/ and pytest tests/infrastructure/test_jwks.py tests/mcp/test_auth.py -v", "branch": "task/task_a0b6ce/wave-3-add-oauth-21", "attempt": 1, "failed_validators": [{"validator_id": "qa-unit", "severity": "blocker", "justification": "Tests failed (exit 127): /bin/sh: pytest: command not found"}, {"validator_id": "qa-lint", "severity": "blocker", "justification": "Tests failed (exit 127): /bin/sh: ruff: command not found"}], "files_changed": ["src/hello.py", "tests/test_hello.py", "git_commit"], "timestamp": "2026-06-21T17:05:04.761660+00:00"}, "task_956c84": {"spec": "\nINTENT: Create a standalone JWKS client that fetches RS256 public keys from mcp-auth.snodo.dev and verifies Bearer JWTs. This is the foundational building block for OAuth 2.1 authentication on the tunnel MCP server.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Create snodo/infrastructure/jwks.py with a class that:\n  - Fetches JWKS from https://mcp-auth.snodo.dev/.well-known/jwks.json at startup\n  - Caches the RS256 public key identified by kid=mcp-auth-rs256-v1\n  - Provides a verify(token) method that returns the decoded payload dict on success, None on failure\n  - Validates: RS256 signature, exp claim (must not be expired), iat claim (must be present)\n  - Handles errors gracefully: network failure, HTTP error, wrong kid, expired token, tampered signature all return None with a warning print to stderr\n  - Is self-contained (no imports from snodo.mcp or snodo.cli)\n  - Uses httpx for HTTP, PyJWT's jwt.decode for verification, jwt.algorithms.RSAAlgorithm.from_jwk for JWK-to-key conversion\n- Create tests/infrastructure/test_jwks.py with tests for:\n  - Successful JWKS fetch caches the public key\n  - Network failure returns False\n  - HTTP error returns False\n  - JWKS with wrong kid returns False\n  - Valid RS256 JWT passes verification\n  - Expired JWT fails verification\n  - Tampered JWT fails verification\n  - verify before fetch returns None\n  - Must generate real RS256 keypairs using cryptography.hazmat and real JWTs using PyJWT for testing\n  - Must mock httpx.get to simulate the JWKS endpoint\n- Do NOT modify any existing files\n- Do NOT create oauth_verifier.py or any transport/CLI changes\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:\n1. pytest tests/infrastructure/test_jwks.py -v --tb=short passes all tests\n2. ruff check snodo/infrastructure/jwks.py passes\n3. python3 -c 'from snodo.infrastructure.jwks import JwksClient, JWKS_KID, JWKS_URI; print(\"OK\")' works\n", "branch": "task/task_956c84/intent-create-a-standalone-jwks", "attempt": 1, "failed_validators": [{"validator_id": "qa-unit", "severity": "blocker", "justification": "Tests failed (exit 127): /bin/sh: pytest: command not found"}, {"validator_id": "qa-lint", "severity": "blocker", "justification": "Tests failed (exit 127): /bin/sh: ruff: command not found"}], "files_changed": ["src/hello.py", "tests/test_hello.py", "git_commit"], "timestamp": "2026-06-21T17:13:06.326619+00:00"}}}, "previous_hash": "ad74e7d61db43d220885e1d34e9b78f47dead5a1ba907452bf6e1abd392fa094", "event_hash": "7d3f27f17e7370c8e891439c3124a56017851f6992ee7e474021d772e8ea6fe0"}
